               <p>Charles Hills. I <rs id="t17740112-38-viclabel198" type="occupation">keep a public house</rs>
                  <join result="persNameOccupation" targOrder="Y" targets="t17740112-38-victim408 t17740112-38-viclabel198"></join>; the prisoner lodged at my house; he went out and took away the key of the room; I heard him come in some time after; then he went away, and I missed the things; I suspected him, and I took him at the Bull and Mouth in Drury-lane the Wednesday following, and delivered him to the constable; then he owned the taking of the things, and named the places where he pawned the shirt, great coat, and marrow spoon.</p>
               <p>The several pawnbrokers produced the different articles.</p>
               <p>The prisoner in his defence acknowledged the charge, said he had been <rs id="t17740112-38-deflabel199" type="occupation">mate of a ship</rs>
